name: Robert Mardini
tweet: #UNSC and the int‚Äôl community, must redouble efforts to prevent wars from happening. Equally important, when wars do happen, they must do their utmost so that parties, and those that support them, respect and ensure respect for IHL. This reduces suffering and preserves dignity.

name: Robert Mardini
tweet: One of the purposes of the #UN as set out in the Charter is to solve international problems of a humanitarian character. To this end, #UNSC addresses humanitarian concerns in armed conflict. It maintains international peace and security and addresses humanitarian concerns.

name: Robert Mardini
tweet: Where circumstances permit, advance warning must be given for attacks that may affect civilians. If there is a choice between military objectives offering a similar military advantage, the option causing least danger to civilians and civilian objects must be selected.

name: Robert Mardini
tweet: Under IHL, an attack must be cancelled if it becomes apparent that it‚Äôs prohibited. Parties must refrain from attack when the expected harm to civilians and civilian objects outweighs military advantage sought.  It thereby becomes a disproportionate, unlawful, attack under IHL.

name: Robert Mardini
tweet: Under IHL, parties must take precautions in attack and against effects of attack to spare civilians and civilian objects. And, indeed, certain objects, such as medical units/transports, cultural property, and objects indispensable to civilian survival, have specific protections.

name: Robert Mardini
tweet: The #UN Charter includes rules on going to war in the first place ‚Äì the jus ad bellum. IHL applies in war ‚Äì the jus in bello. These two distinct bodies of law complement each other to prevent wars, on the one hand, and to better protect people in the case of war, on the other.
